commit.message: indicate usage for python3.6 in readme

Bump version to 3.3.2

Shouldn't have deleted PyPI entry for 3.3.1... can't reupload, so now
have to bump to 3.3.2
Fix list formatting in release notes
Change back the download_url to http, to not break upload_docs
Add release notes for 3.3.1
Change download_url to use https
Change version number from 3.3.0 to 3.3.1

Update doctests to not depend on dictionary iteration order

Adding a lot of sorted, now that dicts iterate in random order and tests
make sure of it.

Fix the csvjoin and csvjoin_test on Windows

Windows requires lineterminator="\n" to csv.writer, and
NamedTemporaryFile prevents csvjoin.py from also reading the file, so
using temp dir instead.
Update tox tests to use Python 3.6
Ignore cache directory
Add DeprecationWarning for iconv, ngrams, ngrams_pad

Merge pull request #8 from humburg/duplicate-delete

Remove duplicates prior to removal of ngrams
Remove duplicates prior to removal of ngrams
Add MANIFEST.in to create complete source distribution
Add link to GitHub issue tracker
Update readme to link to release notes.
Update docs to say 3.3 instead of 3.2
Split index into intro and releasenotes pages
Correct the description field - manual, not first line of README
Correct README description of key function
Add release notes for 3.3.0
Correct docstring formatting in ngram.py
Correct documentation: default is no transform, not str()
Set version 3.3.0 in setup.py

Add missing set methods to NGram class.

The remaining methods of the set class have been overridden
to return NGram instances and maintain NGram state:

* pop - maintains index
* clear - maintains index
* union - returns NGram
* intersection - returns NGram
* difference - returns NGram
* symmetric_difference - returns NGram

Additionally did some fixes:

* intersection_update - accept multiple args

Also modifications:

* copy - accept optional "items" param to use different data
Update 2to3 tests and params in setup.py
